The paper proposes a computation strategy that leverages ideas from coding theory to efficiently deal with straggling workers in a distributed system. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with matrix multiplication and convolution, which are common topics in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also leverages the algebraic structure of polynomial codes, which suggests that it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes an optimal design for high dimensional coded matrix multiplication, which suggests that it may also belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
